research_municipality_step.notes: Clifton, Texas operates under a General Law, Type A, form of city government, seating six elected officials on the City Council with two-year rotating terms. The elected officials and their roles were primarily identified from the City of Clifton's official website and corroborated with the Texas Municipal League directory and Texas State Directory. There was a minor discrepancy regarding one alderman's name between the City of Clifton website and other directories; the City of Clifton's website was prioritized for current officials.
